label: Papercut of Gay a Couple
name: Sewn
discription: In Sewn, Xiyadie’s blood threads into flames as he sits atop a sword, holding in torment and agony as he looks with affection at the photograph of his former lover.

label: Painting of Penis
name: Dingding
discription: Wei presents an alternative phallic representations of penis from a childlike perspective.

label: Poster of Lesbian Couple
name: Commemorate
discription: By using the format of the Chinese commercial calendar poster in Shanghai in the 1930s, Shi Tou convey the relationship between females and elaborate on the status quo of human society.

label: Photo of Male Bodies
name: September
discription: This is a one-year shooting plan. Ren Hang plans to publish one photo book every month. All about survival and love.

label: Installation with Red Capsule
name: Media
discription: Exploring neuroqueerness, Zeng demonstrates this installation piece designed by Burong with tubes, water pumps, red paint and sculpture as a backdrop for the theatre adaptation of Medea.
